[[Humboldt State University]], located in Northern California, has a rich history of sustainability projects such as the [[CCAT|Campus Center for Appropriate Technology]], a student run and lived in, on campus sustainability demonstration house since 1978, and the [[Humboldt Energy Independence Fund (HEIF)|Humboldt Energy Independence Fund]], an association of stakeholders (students, faculty, etc.) working towards the shared goal of attaining energy independence at HSU while providing unique educational opportunities for students since 2007.

